	<text id="material" x="37" y="65" width="683" height="346" autosize="" style="WIZARD_TEXT" visible="true" fx="SHOW" hidefx="HIDE" scroll="AUTO">
		<content translate="true">&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;B&gt;Discussion Topic&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;Because the book availability in low-income neighborhoods is only 1 book per 300 children, helping parents find access to these resources could be a very important part of your role as an educator.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;B&gt;Exploring Resources &lt;/B&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;When working with parents with limited resources, brainstorm a list of resources for print materials available in your local area.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;TEXTFORMAT BLOCKINDENT="16"&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;Possible Resources include:&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/TEXTFORMAT&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Community library&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;School library&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Community centers with resources for children&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Used book store&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Free newspapers or magazines&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;B&gt;Setting Goals&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;After the brainstorming session, challenge the parents to visit one of these resources during the upcoming week. Emphasize the importance of reading as a way to help children expand their vocabularies and prepare them to read independently.&lt;B&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/P&gt;</content>
	</text>
